	<item>
		<title>Plone 4 responsive adaptive theme</title>
		<link>http://www.mastrolinux.com/index.php/2012/01/plone-responsive-theme/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 13 Jan 2012 17:54:18 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>mastro</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.mastrolinux.com/?p=7</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[caption id="attachment_20" align="alignleft" width="173" caption="plone 4 mobile theme"]<a href="http://www.mastrolinux.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/plone4-mobile-preview.png"><img class=" wp-image-20 " title="plone4-mobile-preview" src="http://www.mastrolinux.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/plone4-mobile-preview.png" alt="plone 4 mobile theme" width="173" height="279" /></a>[/caption]

Every time a client ask us a mobile theme, we must check the compatibility with a lot of browsers and devices. The definitive solution for quickly develop a mobile theme, is to write a responsive theme.

A video of the adaptive theme is available here <a title="Plone 4 adaptive theme" href="http://youtu.be/z5lDxxFRMpE" target="_blank">http://youtu.be/z5lDxxFRMpE</a><iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/z5lDxxFRMpE" frameborder="0" width="560" height="315"></iframe>
<!--more-->

You have to keep in mind that all your site must be browsable by a mobile device without worring about which type it is. Mock up firstly for little screen and then try to expand the theme by thinking: "mobile theme must be polished, why should not be the same for the desktop?". Users want semplicity, take a look at google.com.

A really good adaptive theme for Plone 4 is viewable here: <a title="Arpa Plone 4 adaprive theme" href="http://www.arpa.piemonte.it/" target="_blank">http://www.arpa.piemonte.it/</a>. It has three available views: one for large resolutions (desktop), another one for mid-res (Android tablet, iPad, ecc.) and the third for mobile devices. These theme uses <a title="Css media queries" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-mediaqueries/" target="_blank">http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-mediaqueries/</a> and some javascript tools like <a title="Modernizr javascript library" href="http://www.modernizr.com/" target="_blank">http://www.modernizr.com/</a>

