	<item>
		<title>A fabulous Plone 4 theme by Jarn</title>
		<link>http://www.mastrolinux.com/index.php/2012/02/a-fabulous-plone-theme-by-jarn/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 24 Feb 2012 12:37:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>mastro</dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.mastrolinux.com/?p=37</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[caption id="" align="alignleft" width="132" caption="The black and white Jarn logo"]<a href="http://www.jarn.com/en?set_language=en"><img title="The Jarn Logo" src="http://www.jarn.com/++theme++jarn.com/img/logo_landscape_bw.png" alt="The Jarn Logo" width="132" height="51" /></a>[/caption]

Few days ago <a href="http://www.jarn.com">jarn.com</a> as published an impressive Plone responsive theme with an intensive use of js and canvas.
The first elegant effect is the Jarn logo itself: it protrudes outside the menu bar in desktop view and portait tablet visualization.

<!--more-->
<h2>Canvas and images</h2>
Another simple but smart effect is obtained by saturating the images in home page via canvas. The hoover effect give us fully coloured images, let's try this effect by ponting your mouse on an image.
<h2>The rotated image</h2>
[caption id="attachment_45" align="alignleft" width="150" caption="The Jarn team rotated image"]<a href="http://www.mastrolinux.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/jarn-rotated-image.png"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-45" title="jarn-rotated-image" src="http://www.mastrolinux.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/jarn-rotated-image-150x150.png" alt="jarn-rotated-image" width="150" height="150" /></a>[/caption]

In the up-right corner you can see a rotated image of the Jarn team, the effect is obtained using the css3 feature:
<pre> <code>img { -moz-transform: rotate(4deg);</code>
       ...
 }</pre>
and it is nice!

&nbsp;
<h2>The menu</h2>
[caption id="attachment_55" align="alignleft" width="150" caption="The Jarn site menu"]<a href="http://www.mastrolinux.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/jarn-menu1.png"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-55 " title="The Jarn menu" src="http://www.mastrolinux.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/jarn-menu1-150x150.png" alt="The Jarn menu" width="150" height="150" /></a>[/caption]

The menu in desktop size is really simple but it becomes beautiful when you see it with a mobile device. Every menu item is converted in a big button for easy access using your finger on a tablet or phone. The light color (green) it is easy to read in every light conditions.
The searchbar like stackoverflow
The color band gradients
The footer

&nbsp;
<h2>The search bar</h2>
The effect of the search bar is similar to the one available at <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/">http://stackoverflow.com/</a> but has two small defects.

<strong>Edit: Please read the comments posted by the author of the website for further information about this features.</strong>
<ol>
	<li>You have to click the search icon to expand the search bar, there is not the autofocus on the search. This could be a feature for this site, because there are not many contents, the search bar is not so useful for the visitors.</li>
	<li>The lack of interface is about the expansion of the search bar. It overlaps the menu and you have to click again the icon to abandon the search.</li>
</ol>
<h2>The footer</h2>
The footer has a look similar to two buttons. The mobile experience is good, you spontaneously want to touch the mailto button.
<h2>Conclusions</h2>
Beyond these small and questionable defects the site is by now one of the best example of Plone 4 adaptive design. Thank you Jarn, you are really helping the Plone community.]]></content:encoded>
