			<wp:comment_content><![CDATA[Hi. Thanks for this review of jarn.com! I am glad you like the site and like the way it behaves and looks. I am not sure I agree with the points about the search though ;) Let me explain this please :)

First of all, the decisions made about how it behaves and what experience it should bring, have been thoroughly thought through. But I do agree that some might find some of our decisions questionable.

 - So, the autofocus. I don't know why you say there is no auto-focus when clicking the search button. It should work and does for me. So when one clicks a search icon, the field is expanded and the auto-focus happens. If it doesn't, please let me know in what browser does it happen.

 - The fact that the search overlaps the navigation. This is conscious decision. When you expand the search, in 90% of the cases you want to search. That means you, probably, will not click a navigation link and the search button at the same time. we have tried to "isolate" tasks on the site to make it easier to use.

 - And, yes, we have not that many content, so search is secondary here. And that was the reason we hid it behind the button and not expose it to be visible in full-width all the time.

Thanks a lot for the review!]]></wp:comment_content>
