			<wp:comment_content><![CDATA[Thank you for having read the article. I think most users are used to have the search bar active and with autofocus without having to click it. But this is a design choice, and you have made your respectable choice. 
When I click the button in the homepage the autofocus works perfectly on every browser, but when I go to the url: http://www.jarn.com/no/@@search?SearchableText= or to http://www.jarn.com/no/@@search?SearchableText=test I have to click again to have the focus, is this correct?
I experienced some issue on webkit for mobile (iphone and similar) with small screen view. 
Thank you for explaining the searchbar overlap feature, I hope every plone company see your site and use it to be inspired for a good design.
You are welcome!
